Waves of globalization reflect the historical technical progress and modern 
economic growth. The dynamics of this process are here approached using the 
multidimensional scaling (MDS) methodology to analyze the evolution of GDP per 
capita, international trade openness, life expectancy, and education tertiary 
enrollment in 14 countries. MDS provides the appropriate theoretical concepts 
and the exact mathematical tools to describe the joint evolution of these 
indicators of economic growth, globalization, welfare and human development of 
the world economy from 1977 up to 2012. The polarization dance of countries 
enlightens the convergence paths, potential warfare and present-day rivalries in 
the global geopolitical scene.

